<h3>12:16 Exequiries of more than 250 000 persons
The competent authorities inform that, while the funeral of Pope Francis ends, there are over 250,000 people. It makes known the Vatican press room.&nbsp;
<h3>11:59 Thousands of the faithful behind the transenne await courto</h3>
Thousands of faithful are gathered behind the transenne along the six-kilometre route that will be crossed by the funeral procession of Pope Francis. From the monitors - visible in the center for the management of the Great Events of the Questura of Rome - you see the crowd along the streets that from San Pietro lead to Santa Maria Maggiore.&nbsp;
<h3>11:52 At Carmelina esequie, the "sweet with yellow flowers"</h3>
It is present in St. Peter's Square to give the last greeting to Pope Francis, also Carmela Mancuso, for all the "signora con fiori gialli". "Carmelina", a former 78-year-old Calabrian teacher from Monterosso but in Rome for six years, had been greeted by Pope Francis from the balcony of the Gemelli Hospital on the day he finished his shelter. In the 38 days of decency, Carmelina had brought to the Pontiff a bouquet of yellow roses. Francis, on the very day of his departure from the Twins, deviated the path that would take him to Santa Marta to get to Santa Maria Maggiore to make the flowers pose in front of the icon of the Salus Populi Romani.
<h3>11:40 Also Julian Assange in St. Peter's Square
There is also Julian Assange, founder of Wikileaks and released only last year from an almost twenty-year judiciary, in St. Peter's Square for the funeral of Pope Francis. Assange, in a black jacket and tie with white shirt, is at the bottom of via della Conciliazione con la famiglia, and was immortalized by photos and videos spread on social media.
<h3>11:36 For safety leave S.Pietro before Usa and Ukraine</h3>
They will leave Piazza San Pietro for the first delegations of greater interest in security. It is learned from the Questura of Rome. It is Usa, Ukraine, Palestine, France, Spain, English reals, Brazil and the President of the Republic Sergio Mattarella. All others will wait for the exit of the funeral procession in the Vatican. "It will be the minutes to mark the chesss of the exit of the foreign delegations and the funeral procession from the Vatican City State - they explain -. The order of priority decided by the vertical authority will be translated into operational terms on the national territory by the Heads of Police. Remodulation of safety devices is ongoing to facilitate the outflow that are where Piazza Pia and towards Piazza Risorgimento".
<h3>11:21 Zelensky at funeral with shirt and jacket
Ukrainian president, Volodymyr Zelensky, arrived at the funeral of Pope Francis in St. Peter's Square in dark dresses, instead of the usual green mimetic. Always in military style, but wearing a shirt (and not a T-shirt) under the black jacket. The jacket has front pockets and a more informal cut than a classic dress. At the foot of the dark boots. Before the ceremony, Zelensky had a brief interview with American President Donald Trump.
During his last visit to the White House he had been criticized for presenting himself in the Studio Oval without tie and with a military mesh. Some Russian media accuse him of violating the galactic by not presenting himself in an elegant dress at the solemn ceremony for Pope Francis.
<h3>11:05 Applause to S. Maria Maggiore for peace</h3>
Great applause to Santa Maria Maggiore on the request for peace against the horrors of war. The crowd present also in the vicinity of the Basilica, where the feretro of Pope Francis will arrive for burial, listens to the funeral homily transmitted by the maxi screens and applauds on several occasions. Not only for the invocation of peace, in every part of the world, but also for the importance of building bridges and not walls exhorted so many times by Bergoglio during his pontificate. And at the end of the homily, another long applause.&nbsp;

<h3>&nbsp;10:56 Cardinal Re, "His strong exhortation to build bridges and not walls"</h3>
"'Building bridges and not walls' is an exhortation he has repeatedly repeated and the service of faith as Successor of the Apostle Peter has always been combined with the service of man in all its dimensions." Thus Cardinal Giovanni Battista Re.
