Exceptional safety measures for the funeral of Pope Francis> scheduled today at 10 am in St. Peter's Square. Around the area, divided into five areas, public transport block and Rcd> anti-drone systems supplied to the Army and the Air Force. Adopt jammer systems to neutralize suspicious cell phones as potential ordnance remote controls. On the palaces are chosen shooters while around the area there are bombers, cynophiles and river police destined for the patrol of the Tiber and the docks.<br> The Provincial Committee for Order and Public Security in Prefecture has emerged that about four thousand men and women of the law enforcement forces of which over a thousand employees will be employed to escort the 164 foreign delegations present > (of which half include heads of state or government). In addition to these, four thousand volunteers, as well as at least two thousand street workers and to ensure that road closures are respected to the passage of the presidential courts. The security device provides helicopters of law enforcement forces > constantly in flight, while on the ground there will be police patrols, anti-terrorism and anti-sabotage units. Check also in the underground, with stationary offices of special teams in the stations and tunnels of the metro, as well as on the Tiber. Particular attention, of course, to the protection of foreign delegations with the Parioli district practically armored for 24 hours> for the presence of US President Donald Trump at Villa Taverna>. Finally, there will be 50 ambulances of the Ares 118, 6 advanced medical points and over 20 teams of firefighters, even with Nbcr means for the detection of toxic and radioactive substances.
