Argentina president Javier Milei arrived at Fiumicino airport. Tomorrow the president will be in the front row to the funeral of Pope Francis, born in Argentina.&nbsp;
Real Jordan and Denmark arrived at Fiumicino
The rulers of Jordan, King Abdallah II with his wife Rania>, and Queen Mary of Denmark>, arrived at Fiumicino airport. Tomorrow, together with many other rulers, heads of state and prime ministers, will attend the funeral of Pope Francis.&nbsp;
<h2>250 thousand people paid tribute to salma</h2>
From Wednesday morning 23 April to 11:00 until last night at 19:00 > they went to St. Peter's Basilica to greet Pope Francis about 250,000 people. It makes known the Vatican press room.&nbsp;
<h2>Emmanuel Macron and his wife Brigitte in S.Pietro</h2>
French President Emmanuel Macron and his wife Brigitte in San Pietro paid tribute to the psalm of Pope Francis. The head of the Elysée stopped a few minutes in front of the coffin.
