The Direction of the Museums > and Cultural Heritage >, "in expressing deep mourning and pain for the disappearance of the Holy Father", we read, that Saturday, 26 April, "the Vatican Museums > and the Museum of Castel Gandolfo > will be closed to the public, as a sign of mourning, for the funeral of the Roman Pontiff Francis".
<h2> The cardinals at the tomb of Francis at S.M.Maggiore</h2>
On Sunday afternoon at 4 pm the cardinals will go to the Basilica of Santa Maria Maggiore. After passing the Holy Door, they will visit the tomb of Pope Francis and the chapel where there is the icon of the Salus Populi Romani > and then the Vespers will be celebrated. At 18 they will return to the Vatican.&nbsp;
