AGI - During the rite of the closure of the coffin a veil of white silk is placed to cover the face of the Pope>. Inside the coffin are inserted a bag with coins > minted during its pontificate >, silver and bronze medals to symbolize years of service. In addition, a metal tube containing the Rogito > will be placed, prepared by the master of ceremonies, in which the life of the Pope is told.
This is what the Ordo Exsequiarum Romani Pontificis> provides. The rite takes place in the presence of Cardinal Camerlengo>, Kevin Farrell. Among others, Cardinal Mauro Gambetti, the cardinal already Secretary of State, Pietro Parolin, the Vicar for the Diocese of Rome > Baldo Reina, the Deputy Secretary of State, Monsignor Edgar Pena Parra, the Elemosiniere of His Holiness, Cardinal Konrad Krajewski and the family members of the deceased.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
<h2> Bara</h2>
At the end of the rite is placed the lid to the casket of zinc on which are the cross, the coat of arms of the late Pontiff > and the plate bearing the name of the Pontiff, the duration of his life and his Petrine ministry. The zinc coffin is soldered and the seals of Cardinal Camerlengo, the Prefecture of the Pontifical House, the Office of Liturgical Celebrations and the Vatican Chapter are engraved. The wooden coffin is also closed. On the cover are the cross and the coat of arms of the deceased Pontiff.
The rite ends with the recitation of eternal rest and the Salve Regina>. Bergoglio wanted to cancel the custom of the three coffins. The rite is therefore leaner. For the previous pontiffs, the rite predicted that the cypress wood case was linked with red ribbons on which the seals of the Apostolic Chamber, the Prefecture, the Celebrations and the Vatican Chapter were engraved. The first coffin was dropped in a galvanized case and then in another of wood (noce or oak) with the same seals and, above, the cross and the coat of arms of the deceased pontiff.
&nbsp;
